📝 Sample Preface Outline (with Callouts)

Here’s a proposed narrative flow:
	1.	Opening Vignette — A brief anecdote: e.g., “In 2015, a multi-million-dollar integration project derailed because two teams used different definitions of “acceptance”… I learned how brittle the “invisible joints” are.” (VP Reflection)
	2.	Why This Manual Exists — What needs did you experience that no other book/manual addressed, especially in enterprise scale.
	3.	What This Manual Is & Isn’t — Clarify scope, not substitute for hands-on decision, not a plug-and-play tool. (Why This Matters)
	4.	Intended Readers & How to Use It — Paths (e.g. read sequentially vs. dip by topic). (Pro Tip)
	5.	Terminology & Styles — Key terms defined, the callout styles (VP Insight, From the Field, etc). (Caution)
	6.	How to Read / Navigate — e.g., use appendices, search for dashboards first, refer to rituals early. (From the Field)
	7.	Acknowledgments & Version Note — Who contributed; versioning intent
	8.	Signature / Date — to mark this manual’s birth moment

