✔️ What We Agree the Preface Should Do (Common Understanding)
	•	It welcomes the reader, sets tone, and begins the coach-to-reader relationship.
	•	It frames the manual’s intent and boundaries (what it will and will not solve).
	•	It orients the reader: how to use, how to consume, and how to adapt.
	•	It introduces guiding conventions and callout styles.
	•	It contains a few wisdom layers to ground authority and empathy.

